The effects of increasing concentrations of seven essential oils on mycelial growth of the fungi 
 A. alternata and 
 S. cucurbitacearum were investigated. These essential oils were from various sources, and are defined as (see 
 Table 1): 
 C.cit, 
 Cymbopogon citratus (lemon grass); 
 L.dent, 
 Lavandula dentata (lavender); 
 L.hyb, 
 Lavandula hybrida (lavandin); 
 M.alt, 
 Melaleuca alternifoglia (tea tree); 
 L.nob, 
 Laurus nobilis (bay laurel); 
 O.maj1/2, 
 Origanum majorana 1/2 (majoram).
